  "text": "It has been shown in [CITATION_1] that a controller of the form u(t) = f (Xp) (with f is a Lipschitz continuous function) leads to a better disturbance attenuation than a controller of the form u(t) = f (xp) for a wide class of perturbations. In next subsection, previous considerations are extended to the partial state measurement case.",
